cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper discusses the architecture and topology of 3D underwater sensor networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication in computer science. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses energy efficiency and frequency reuse, which are related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The nonhierarchical approach mentioned in the paper involves randomly deployed nodes, which is related to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper also discusses the optimality of the proposed scheme, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
